Package org.firstinspires.ftc.teamcode Description

The location where all LCR code will be placed. If you're just learning, here are some tips for basic program creation. In Android Studio:
  1. Open the package org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcontroller.external.samples.
  2. In that package, there are a bunch of sample classes that showcase different things you can code. Find one that suits your needs, and copy everything in the file.
  3. Rightclick (or two-finger click) on the folder "org.firstinspires.ftc.teamcode"
  4. New -&rt; Java Class
  5. Type whatever name you want to call your code, and click OK.
  6. Delete everything, and paste the sample into your file.
  7. Replace line 1 with this: 
    package org.firstinspires.ftc.teamcode;
  8. Change the name after the word class to the name you chose. (Capitalization matters!)
  9. Save your work!
  10. Take a look at the code. FTC does a good job of commenting, so see if you can get a general understanding of what's going on.
  11. Once you feel like you have a good idea of how to use this code, tweak it to your own needs. (Change the numbers, add more movements, etc.) If you still aren't sure, come talk to Noah or Gabe.
  12. Save your work!
  13. From the top menu: VCS -&rt; Git -&rt; Add
  14. VCS -&rt; Commit. In Commit Message, summarize what your code does.
  15. Click the arrow next to the Commit button, and click Commit and Push.
  16. Push, and you're done!
